 </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> spells are things that let you interact with the environment to accomplish a goal of some sort. To me, they're no different than armor or a sword with a level requirement to equip.<br><br>As an example take pre-velious armor. If I'm level 60 why shouldn't I have a trak BP? Well, only the best most mobile guilds can kill him first so I never have a shot. What happens is I have to wait until either a) everyone gets what they want and stop killing him long enough for me to have a shot, or b) I buy what I want from someone who has killed him. Much like high level spells are now. The only difference is that someone might want armor or a weapon for a twink. <br><br>The obvious solution is no drop spells, except that doing that would remove all extra copies from the market and people would still kill the spell dropping mobs for whatever loot/spells they still needed. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uedeina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edeina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Board Mistress</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/9/02 10:07:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=793.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.one.se/users/chribesk/edeina.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Mmm, a old but still interesting debate.<br>Remember the outrage when Kunark was released?<br><br>LOL, I remember the problems with CoH for us mages. The guild I was in really needed CoH mages. I was leveling as fast as I could and tried my best to buy the spell. However, the only person I found who had one for trade demanded a hierophants cloak for it. (By then that was a very rare item and the by far best back slot item for many classes.) I would have traded if I owned a cloak, but i didn't.<br><br>We was three magicians in the guild.<br><br>*Me, atending on all raids and about to get out of level 54.<br>*A level 60 mage who was a bad player and scewed up the raids he did attend with his constant whining and total lack of petcontrol. A nice guy actually, but incompetent in many ways.<br>*A level 55 mage who was a comptent mage and a extremely nice person, but who NEVER showed up for raids. He was also one of my best friends.<br><br>One of my fellow guild officers led a small xp group in Sebilis. No mage in the group, I was online elsewhere soloing for xp. The officer was one of my best friends, and the RP girlfriend of the level 55 mage. She decided that he would have the spell. So far so good, but a few hours later the second in command of the guild logged in, and she and the officer had a huge quarrel about it on guildchat. The officer almost disguilded, but in the end she stayed and I got the spell and dinged 55 the next day.<br><br>A few weeks later the 55 mage was trying to organize a efreeti camp group, he needed a pair of EBoots as part of a trade for his own CotH scroll. The efreeti was camped like it always was back in those days, and I doubt we had been able to put together a group that could have made it. Most in the guild was 53 or lower, and few was online at that hour anyway. I gave him my EBoots and he got the scroll.<br><br>The level 60 mage bought his CoH scroll for 250 RL dollars.<br><br>These days almost all level 55 mages have their CoH scrolls allready, as a gift or a reasonably cheap trade. <p>Love, Edeina<br>Highelf Arch Mage of Erollisi.<br>Citizen of <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero">Ayonae Ro</a>, member of <a href="http://pub23.ezboa